BRCA.subtype <- TCGAquery_subtype(tumor = "brca")
## brca subtype information from:doi.org/10.1016/j.ccell.2018.03.014
BRCA_Subtypes<-data.frame(Patients=BRCA.subtype$patient,Subtypes=BRCA.subtype$BRCA_Subtype_PAM50)

PAM50_Genes<-read.table("PAM50_Genes.txt",header = FALSE,col.names = "Genes")

BRCA_Expression<-rnaseq.RPKM.BRCA$dat

View(BRCA_Expression)

PAM50_Expression<-BRCA_Expression[PAM50_Genes$Genes,]

#what are unique sample vial comnbination within barcodes
library(stringr)
unique(str_sub(colnames(PAM50_Expression), 14,16))
## [1] "01A" "11A" "11B" "06A" "01B"
# locate non duplicated patient code by omiting strings from sample vials to end 
PAM50_Expression_unique<-PAM50_Expression[,!duplicated(gsub("-01A-.*|-01B-.*|-11A-.*|-11B-.*|-06A-.*|-06B-.*","",colnames(PAM50_Expression)))]

# rename colnames by omiting strings from sample vials to end
colnames(PAM50_Expression_unique)<-gsub("-01A-.*|-01B-.*|-11A-.*|-11B-.*|-06A-.*|-06B-.*","",colnames(PAM50_Expression_unique))

# match pt names from subtypes df and exp paitient names
Overlap_Samples<-intersect(BRCA_Subtypes$Patients,colnames(PAM50_Expression_unique))

PAM50_Expression_clean<-PAM50_Expression_unique[,match(Overlap_Samples,colnames(PAM50_Expression_unique))]

PAM50_Subtype_clean<-BRCA_Subtypes[match(Overlap_Samples,BRCA_Subtypes$Patients),]

write.table(PAM50_Expression_clean,file = "BRCA_PAM50_Expression.txt",sep = ",",col.names = TRUE,row.names = TRUE,quote = FALSE)
write.table(PAM50_Subtype_clean,file = "BRCA_Subtypes.txt",sep = ",",col.names = TRUE,row.names = TRUE,quote = FALSE)
BRCA_PAM50_Expression<-read.table("BRCA_PAM50_Expression.txt",sep = ",",header = TRUE)

colnames(BRCA_PAM50_Expression)<-gsub("\\.","-",colnames(BRCA_PAM50_Expression))

# Make sure the samples are identical between the two data set
BRCA_Subtypes<-read.table("BRCA_Subtypes.txt",sep = ",",header = TRUE)
BRCA_Subtypes$Patients==colnames(BRCA_PAM50_Expression)

#subset rownames with choosen 3 subtype biomarkers
Subtype_Biomarkers<-c("ERBB2","ESR1","PGR")

Biomarkers_Expression<-BRCA_PAM50_Expression[Subtype_Biomarkers,]

#transpose to have gene features as column names, patients as rownames
Biomarkers_Expression<-as.data.frame(t(Biomarkers_Expression))

#add subtype column in exp df
Biomarkers_Expression$Subtypes<-BRCA_Subtypes$Subtypes

Biomarkers_Expression[,1:3]<-log1p(Biomarkers_Expression[,1:3])

Biomarkers_Expression$Subtypes<-as.factor(Biomarkers_Expression$Subtypes)
library(caret)
## Warning: package 'caret' was built under R version 4.1.2
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Loading required package: lattice
# 80% of rows used for training
set.seed(1)
index <- createDataPartition(Biomarkers_Expression$Subtypes, p=0.80, list=FALSE)
Training_Data <- Biomarkers_Expression[index,]

#20% for test
Test_Data <- Biomarkers_Expression[-index,]
sapply(Training_Data,class)

# 10-fold cross validation with 3 repeats
trainControl <- trainControl(method="repeatedcv", number=10, repeats=3)
metric <- "Accuracy"
# Linear Discriminant Analysis (lda)
set.seed(600)
fit.lda <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="lda", metric=metric, trControl=trainControl)

# Classification And Regression Tree (cart)
set.seed(600)
fit.cart <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="rpart", metric=metric, trControl=trainControl)

# k-nearest neighbors (knn)
set.seed(600)
fit.knn <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="knn", metric=metric, trControl=trainControl)

# Support vector machines (svm)
set.seed(600)
fit.svm <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="svmRadial", metric=metric, trControl=trainControl)

# Random Forest (rf)
set.seed(600)
fit.rf <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="rf", metric=metric, trControl=trainControl)
## note: only 2 unique complexity parameters in default grid. Truncating the grid to 2 .
results <- resamples(list(lda=fit.lda, cart=fit.cart, knn=fit.knn, svm=fit.svm, rf=fit.rf))
summary(results)

## 866 samples
##   3 predictor
##   5 classes: 'Basal', 'Her2', 'LumA', 'LumB', 'Normal' 
## 
## Pre-processing: Box-Cox transformation (2) 
## Resampling: Cross-Validated (10 fold, repeated 3 times) 
## Summary of sample sizes: 779, 779, 780, 779, 780, 778, ... 
## Resampling results across tuning parameters:
## 
##   C     Accuracy   Kappa    
##   0.25  0.7055819  0.4759635
##   0.50  0.7144213  0.5012565
##   1.00  0.7201957  0.5167737
## 
## Tuning parameter 'sigma' was held constant at a value of 0.7537481
## Accuracy was used to select the optimal model using the largest value.
## The final values used for the model were sigma = 0.7537481 and C = 1.
# 10-fold cross validation with 3 repeats
trainControl <- trainControl(method="repeatedcv", number=10, repeats=3)
metric <- "Accuracy"
set.seed(600)
grid <- expand.grid(.sigma=c(0.025, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15), .C=seq(1, 10, by=1))
fit.svm <- train(Subtypes~., data=Training_Data, method="svmRadial", metric=metric, tuneGrid=grid,
    preProc=c("BoxCox"), trControl=trainControl)
print(fit.svm)
